caption: First place we tried while visiting New Orleans because we wanted Fried Chicken and it was absolutely delicious. Very Crispy, hot and fresh. I also ordered a pina coloda with and extra shot of rum. It was all very pricey but I’d say it was worth it. The two girls running the place were not helpful at all, and not very friendly to us. The four stars are for the food only. If you’re looking for good fried chicken, this is great.
Good chicken. Bad service.  Couldn’t stay off of the phone even to take our order.

There is however one thing that really really annoyed me and that was the fact that you are not able to tip your server on your credit card over $9. Having been a server for over 20 years you know that's ridiculous.

The food was very overpriced, very bland, and it made my whole family sick. We spent $40 on a meal and it was all awful. The chicken was so overcooked that the fried bits were hard as a rock and the chicken itself was dry. The catfish was awful and bland and slightly undercooked, no seasoning, and even though it was fried, it wasn't even crunchy. The fries were awful. 10 out of 10 would not recommend. Ever. Do not eat here. It literally made my mother, father, and me sick. I wish I could give it negative stars, but you have to one star to leave a review. Seriously, if you're going to spend $40 on food, go somewhere that actually has real New Orleans food, and where the locals go. Do your research, don't settle for this.

The food was atrocious and extremely overpriced. 3 people for $50 (water was $8 for the three of us). That money anywhere else in the French Quarter would have got us better quality. The chicken was charred to a brick, the catfish was mushy and flavorless, and the shrimp was rubbery. To top it off about 20 minutes after I ate I spent an hour on the toilet. Never go here, it is horrific.
